Before moving a workload into production, organizations should confirm that operational readiness requirements have been satisfied.

A readiness checklist may include:

* Identity configured
* Security validated
* Monitoring enabled
* Backup configured
* Disaster recovery documented
* Documentation completed
* Cost estimates reviewed
* Performance tested
* Access approvals verified

For example, a production application should not be released until monitoring alerts and backup procedures have been fully tested.

A real-life use case is reducing production incidents by validating operational readiness before deployment.

Operational readiness supports reliable cloud service delivery.
